title: [1991-07-12] Keene, NH (Live Phish 19)
description:
Live Phish Vol. 19 was recorded live at the Colonial Theater in Keene, New Hampshire, on July 12, 1991.

This concert was recorded during the middle of the band's 1991 summer tour with the Giant Country Horns - a three-piece horn section that would learn and perform individual sections of Phish songs during concerts. Two of the three members of the horn section - Dave Grippo and Russell Remington - would go on to perform with Trey Anastasio's solo band in the 21st century.

Rarities include two Charlie Parker covers: the one-time-only performance of "Moose the Mooche" and the Jaco Pastorius-infused "Donna Lee." Drummer Jon Fishman also performs The Doors' "Touch Me," complemented thoroughly by the horn section.
